comment: Shes an amazing prof. Really open to questions and great at giving helpful advice and tips. I definitely recommend her if youre not an acting major. She really helps you with the technicalities of acting. Shes also just a great listener and really easy to talk too.

It's hard to get past the fact that everyone worships her;  but, she isn't all that.  She is conceited and oblivious; she has a total disregard for time, despite her students having other priorities besides her class.  She let's students get away with not taking her assignments seriously, which makes those who do things on time think there's no poi
she is amazing! you learn so much from her! you just gotta listen and you will get it, she works hard for her students and expects the same from them. i cant say i negative thing about her.
Perfection.
ok. maggie is perfect. she is one of my mentors and has changed my life. her class: read what she tells you to read. be completely open. trust her. do the work...it's all worth it. she's incredible
I had Maggie in 2001 and she made the biggest impact on me! I love her!
No Comments
Maggies cool she pushes the students to work hard and is a great way to start studying theatre but, i think she hates me.
Loves her work, and the material she teaches. Gets most of it across to the students. Nice woman to work with.
Sweet lady but occasional mood swings! WHATS UP WITH THE HEAVY WORK LOAD. you'd think we were nursing majors with all this work...
Sweet lady, but needs to stop bringing politics into the classroom, it's getting kinda old. Still very nice and a good teacher
Great Teacher!
a negative word cannot be spoken about her

At first I absolutely hated this class, she seemed bossy and in your face, but once she weeded out the idiots of the class she was an AMAZING professor. I hated social psychologies until this course and will take everything she offers now until I graduate. Don't be afraid to take her classes, it's extrememly dense in reading but you WILL do well.

Professor Steil is a great woman.  She tells it like it is and seems pretty intimidating at first, but you'll quickly realize she's a great person.  She assigns a little too much reading for anyone's tastes, and likes people to participate in class.  She's an extremely fair grader.

All of the people who dropped this class because they were intimidated by Prof Steil made a big mistake.  She only seems scary at first.  She only gave three tests and they weren't that bad as long as you studied the review sheets.  The papers were easy because all you had to write about were your personal experiences.  I would take her again.

She knows her stuff and is very nice once u get into the semester! Good amount of work and u definitely needed to read but learned a lot and had really good discussions. Glad I took the class. Good teacher to know also!

I loved this class, at the beginning I wasn't sure that I made a good decision to take it but I learned so musch from Dr. Steil, and she made the topic fun. Towards the end of the semester she let us in on some real life sexism experiences if her own, she knows of what she speaks!I highly recommend taking a class with Dr. Steil, she's awesome!

Prof. Steil was by far one of the best professors I had at Adelphi.  She is extremely knowledgable about the material and you can tell she loves what she does.  She expects a lot from her students; it is an Advanced class.  There is a lot of reading, but all of it is worth reading, and again, it is an Advanced class, expcet it, don't complain.

I'd have to say she wasnt exactly my favorite teacher, but she grades fair.She gives way too much reading,but does give review sheets b4 the tests..make sure u know these..memorize the answers that u will write 4 the essay part of the test, because she gives u these questions(3 or 4)that r on test
Honors' Seminar: Psychology of Power...awesome class...great professor, very knowledgeable
TOO MUCH READING!avoid this woman. shes boring and expects too much. interesting class but horrible professor!!
interesting class. nice person overall.

I found her to be a very inspiring woman.I thought the class was extremely thought provoking,I enjoyed it. She is not an easy grader but extremely fair. Show her that you are working hard and care she will see that.I think that matters more to her.
Hard grader, way too much reading (remember Professors, your class isn't the only one we are currently enrolled in) and not approachable.  If you can avoid taking her, do so.
Interesting class but I found her tests and papers difficult.  Way too much reading!!!!
